    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1954-05-14T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1954-05-14T00:00:00-05:00" n="314"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d314">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">
                    <gloss target="#t_UNP1">UNP</gloss> files, lot 59 D 237, “Slates”</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Memorandum by the Officer in Charge of General Assembly
                        Affairs</hi> (<persName>
                        <hi rend="italic">Taylor</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>,] <date calendar="gregorian" when="1954-05-14">May 14,
                            1954</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <list type="subject">
                    <item>Subject:</item>
                    <item>Attached Telegram<note n="1" xml:id="d314fn1">Not attached; the telegram
                            was sent out the same date (May 14).</note> Concerning <persName
                            corresp="#p_ZAFRULLAKHANSM1">Sir Zafrullah Khan</persName>’s Candidacy
                        for <gloss target="#t_ICJ1">ICJ</gloss>
                    </item>
                </list>
                <p>This question was considered at a meeting with Mr. <persName
                        corresp="#p_MURPHYRD1">Murphy</persName> yesterday, at which it was decided
                    that instead of informing the Prime Minister now that we would support <persName
                        corresp="#p_ZAFRULLAKHANSM1">Sir Zafrullah</persName> for the <gloss
                        target="#t_ICJ1">ICJ</gloss>, we would state that we considered him well
                    qualified but that we could not commit ourselves on the matter until next month.
                    It was also decided (<gloss target="#t_NEA1">NEA</gloss>, <gloss target="#t_L1"
                        >L</gloss>, <gloss target="#t_UNA1">UNA</gloss> and <gloss target="#t_FE1"
                        >FE</gloss> being present) that we would support <persName
                        corresp="#p_ZAFRULLAKHANSM1">Sir Zafrullah</persName> for this post but
                    would not inform any one of it until after the ILC election on June 4th,</p>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
